<% content_for :head do %>
<title>UI5- progress</title>
<% end %>

<h1>Progress Bars</h1>

<hr class="separator">

<div class="row">
  <div class="span-4">
      <p></p>
      <div id="progress1">
      <div class="progress blue striped-animate">
        <div class="bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="span-8">
    <pre class="brush: html; gutter: false;" data-from="#progress1"></pre>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="separator">

<div class="row">
    <div class="span-4">
        <h2>Progress colors</h2>
        <p>For customize colors, add class <code>blue</code>, <code>green</code>, <code>orange</code>,
            <code>grey</code> or <code>black</code> beside the <code>progress</code> class.</p>
        <div class="progress blue">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 30%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress green">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 40%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress orange">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 50%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress red">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress grey">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 70%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress black">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 80%"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="span-4">
        <h2>Progress striped</h2>
        <p>If you want to have striped affect, add class <code>stripped</code> beside the class <code>progress</code>
            or <code>striped-animate</code> if you want it animates.</p>
        <div class="progress blue striped">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 50%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress green striped-animate">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>

        <h2>Progress sizes</h2>
        <p>For custom sizes, progress bar provides <code>mini</code>, <code>medium</code>, <code>large</code>, <code>x-large</code> sizes.</p>
        <div class="progress blue mini">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 40%"></div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="progress green medium">
            <div class="bar" style="width: 60%"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="span-4">
        <h2>Progress with text inside</h2>
        <p>Follow to the html markup below if you want to show text inside the progress. Remember that you need to fix the progress width.</p>
        <div id="progress22">
          <div class="progress blue striped-animate" style="width: 250px">
            <span class="text">30%</span>
            <div class="bar" style="width: 30%">
              <span class="text" style="width: 250px">30%</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>

        <div class="progress blue striped-animate" style="width: 250px">
            <span class="text">50%</span>
            <div class="bar" style="width: 50%">
                <span class="text" style="width: 250px">50%</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br>

        <div class="progress blue striped-animate" style="width: 250px">
            <span class="text">70%</span>

            <div class="bar" style="width: 70%">
                <span class="text" style="width: 250px">70%</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <pre class="brush: html; gutter: false;" data-from="#progress22"></pre>
    </div>
</div>